{"lemma":"عُثْنُونِ","slug":"عُثْنُونِ","root":"ع.ث.ن","root_slug":"ع-ث-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ث-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28068"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%AB%D9%92%D9%86%D9%8F%D9%88%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"goatee"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rain beginning to fall or wind beginning to blow"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"commencement, first breeze of something","tags":["figuratively","plural","plural-only"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Apparently from the root ع ث ن (ʕ ṯ n) related to fumigation; the beard is an apt place to apply aromates, Ethiopian Semitic ዕጣን (ʿəṭan, “incense”)."},"ipa":["/ʕuθ.nuːn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28068","headword_ar":"عُثْنُونٌ","root":"Evn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Small long hairs under the part beneath the lower jaw of the camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) [pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EavaAniynu","text_ar":"عَثَانِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiyrN *uw EavaAniyna","text_ar":"بَعِيرٌ ذُو عَثَانِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a camel having such small long hairs"},{"kind":"text","text":"], like as they said, for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maforiq","text_ar":"مَفْرِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the head,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafaAriqu","text_ar":"مَفَارِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion thereof that extends beyond the two sides of the cheeks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion that grows upon the chin and beneath it, downwards:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"length of the beard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portion of the beard that depends form the chin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 820:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euvonuwnu All~iHoyapi","text_ar":"عُثْنُونُ اللِّحْيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the extremity of the beard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Certain small hairs at the part in which the he-goat is slaughtered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raEovap","text_ar":"رَعْثَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wattle"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the cock. (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rEv","text_ar":"رعث"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) ―         -b2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first"},{"kind":"text","text":"of wind and of rain; (S, K;) so says [the Imám] Aboo- Haneefeh: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain generally:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain while it is between the heaven and the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EavaAniynu","text_ar":"عَثَانِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) AZ says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEavaAniynu","text_ar":"العَثَانِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rain that is between the clouds and the earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~abalu","text_ar":"السَّبَلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuvonuwnN","text_ar":"عُثْنُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euvonuwnu","text_ar":"عُثْنُونُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aHaAbi","text_ar":"السَّحَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the clouds that have fallen upon the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EavaAniynu Als~aHaAbi","text_ar":"عَثَانِينُ السَّحَابِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pendent skirts of the clouds:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euvonuwnu Alr~iyHi","text_ar":"عُثْنُونُ الرِّيحِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the trail of the wind when it comes drawing along the dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (TA.) And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"first"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (Ham p. 820.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1955}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}